The paper also discusses the likelihood-ratio test and optimization of detection performance, which are concepts related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new cooperation structure for spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves the communication and coordination of multiple nodes. The paper also discusses the probability of false alarm and detection, which are metrics related to network performance. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new architecture for spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves the design and control of a system. The paper also discusses the optimization of detection performance, which is a control problem. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the problem of spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves the security and privacy of wireless communications. The paper also discusses the optimization of detection performance, which is a security-related problem. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a new cooperation structure for spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves the coordination and interaction of multiple agents. The paper also discusses the optimization of detection performance, which is a problem related to multiagent systems.
